{"id": 329, "title": "Ticket #329: Condor-C over-reports RemoteWallClockTime", "description": "<blockquote>\nI noticed that when Condor-C jobs finish, on the submit side, the <code>RemoteWallClockTime</code> stored in the job <code>ClassAd</code> is about double what it should be.</blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2015-Apr-16 11:18:12 by jfrey:</em> <br/>\n\nThis is because the <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=CondorJob\" title=\"Condor Job\">CondorJob</a></span> object in the gridmanager propagates the <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=RemoteWallClockTime\" title=\"Remote Wall Clock Time\">RemoteWallClockTime</a></span> value from the remote job ad into the local job ad in the schedd. Then, when the job completes, BaseJob::UpdateRuntimeStats() adds its own calculation of how long the job's been running (calculated from <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=ShadowBday\" title=\"Shadow Bday\">ShadowBday</a></span> in the local ad).\n\n<p>We should use BaseJob::calcRuntimeStats to eliminate this double-counting of runtime.</p></blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">\n<span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5007\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5007'); return false;\" title=\"Condor-C double-counts runtime when job restarts\">#5007</a></span></td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"center\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon ptr1\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\">\nCondor-C double-counts runtime when job restarts</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Jun-01 13:15</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/005d53918d013bef34ccf953dff8dc38bf12fa15\">[44926]</a></span>: minor 8.2.9 version history item edit <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=329\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('329'); return false;\" title=\"Condor-C over-reports RemoteWallClockTime\">#329</a></span> <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5007\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5007'); return false;\" title=\"Condor-C double-counts runtime when job restarts\">#5007</a></span>  (By Karen Miller )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Apr-30 16:44</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/351cc4c192002809e7a779131faddc998f5378f3\">[44772]</a></span>: Docs for Condor-C runtime double-count bug fix. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=329\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('329'); return false;\" title=\"Condor-C over-reports RemoteWallClockTime\">#329</a></span> <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5007\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5007'); return false;\" title=\"Condor-C double-counts runtime when job restarts\">#5007</a></span>  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n<tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2015-Apr-30 16:44</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/commit/31fcc657c2869d5227d0eb82f628b4ce969ae7cb\">[44771]</a></span>: Don't double count the runtime of Condor-C jobs. <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=329\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('329'); return false;\" title=\"Condor-C over-reports RemoteWallClockTime\">#329</a></span> <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"resolved\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=5007\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('5007'); return false;\" title=\"Condor-C double-counts runtime when job restarts\">#5007</a></span> Instead, take all runtime attributes (including <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=ShadowBday\" title=\"Shadow Bday\">ShadowBday</a></span>) from the remote schedd and don't modify them in the gridmanager.  (By Jaime Frey )</td></tr>\n</tbody></table>", "type": "defect", "last_change": "2015-May-14 16:32", "status": "resolved", "created": "2009-Mar-17 14:23", "fixed_version": "2009-Mar-17 14:23", "broken_version": "v070400", "priority": "3", "subsystem": "Grid", "assigned_to": "jfrey", "derived_from": "", "creator": "danb", "rust": "", "customer_group": "other", "visibility": "public", "notify": "", "due_date": ""}